definitions.definition: To drench or fill with water.
examples: The boat was swamped in the storm.

definitions.definition: To overwhelm ; to make too busy , or overrun the capacity of.
examples: I have been swamped with paperwork ever since they started using the new system.

definitions.definition: To plunge into difficulties and perils; to overwhelm; to ruin; to wreck.
To clear (a road or an area) of brush , particularly so as to create a path for loggers to be able to access trees .

main_definition: To drench or fill with water.
